"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"lgnd\">",
"    The varus stress test is used to determine the integrity of the lateral collateral ligament. One hand is placed above the knee medially and one hand is placed along the lateral gastrocnemius muscle. The upper hand is used to stabilize the thigh while the lower hand places inward pressure on the calf. Pain, movement of the lateral joint space, and the elasticity of the ligament are noted.",
